I will never forget how this moment felt. The grief from losing a loved one can feel debilitating. I couldn’t find the passion I once had for life and for the things I love. I was ready to quit it all. I was afraid none of it mattered in the end. I was wrong. God turned my fears into courage and my doubts into faith and so I decided to keep fighting. It wasn’t easy, but it was worth it & I know now there was purpose in it all. I know that they are in Heaven smiling, knowing that I didn’t give up. To whoever is reading…protect the hope in your heart, turn your fears into courage and keep fighting. 🕊️🤎
